article.linkText: Mazzante gets Penn State rolling to 90-61 victory
article.story:
STATE COLLEGE, Pa. (AP) -- Kelly Mazzante scored 20 of her 33
points in the second half to lead No. 14 Penn State to a 90-61
victory over Siena in the second round of the preseason WNIT on
Sunday.

<photo1>

	   Mazzante, who led the nation in scoring last season, had the
15th 30-point game of her career.

	   Penn State (2-0) will play host to Mississippi State in the
semifinals Wednesday. Mississippi State beat Tulsa 92-66.

	   Penn State coach Rene Portland wasn't concerned that Mazzante
had attempted just one shot midway through the first half.

	   ''She can get herself on a roll,'' Portland said. ''Once she
gets on a roll, we just sit back, watch and smile.''

	   Mazzante had three baskets in an 11-0 run at the start of the
second half. A pull-up jumper from the left wing and a 3-pointer
from the right side gave Mazzante 26 points and pushed Penn State's
lead to 63-43 with 13:46 left.

	   ''We did a good job in the first half against her,'' Siena coach
Gina Castelli said. ''Then she hit two open shots, and we put her
to the line. She hit 11 free throws.''

	   Mazzante shot 11-for-13 from the line.

	   ''Rene told me coming into this season that I needed to get to
the foul line at least 10 times per game, and I think that's where
I've been trying to focus being different from last season,''
Mazzante said. ''I'm still getting double-teamed, but that's
leaving other people open and other people are creating.''

	   All five Penn State starters scored double figures. Jess Strom
finished with 15, Jess Brungo and Tanisha Wright each had 14, and
Ashli Schwab added 11.

	   ''It's easier for her when the whole team can't focus on her,''
Strom said.

	   Siena (1-1) went 8:59 without a field goal in the second half
before Trish Lyons hit 3-pointer with 1:18 left.

	   Siena was in foul trouble early. Gunta Blasko, who had 18 points
and nine rebounds in the Saints' first-round victory over Syracuse,
had three points and one rebound when she fouled out with 15:12
left.

	   ''The first half, we were doing a good job, and then in the
second half we were turning the ball over and their defense just
ignited their offense,'' Castelli said. ''When you start getting
behind, you stop thinking about what you're supposed to be doing
out there.''

	   Liene Jansone scored 12 points for Siena. Jolene Johnston had 11
and Nathalie Marchino 10.

	   Jansone, Marchino and Michelle Blot each hit 3-pointers in an
11-0 run as Siena took a 19-17 lead midway through the first half.
Mazzante converted a pair of free throws with eight minutes left to
give Penn State the lead, and the Lady Lions led 43-37 at halftime.
